  "texts": [
    "It performs monolingual semantic similarity on q tgt to obtain a sentence in L tgt from a parallel dataset D para, then uses monolingual semantic similarity on its pair in L src to find the high-resource exemplars from D src.",
    "Although the monolingual semantic similarity between two sentences from a low-resource language is also suboptimal, this problem can be alleviated by incorporating other similarity metrics such as TF-IDF and bag-of-words.",
    "We denote ICL method using the translation semantic similarity as T-ICL.",
    "We show this analysis in Appendix C along with the depiction of the cross-lingual retrieval methods.",
    "To calculate the cross-lingual and monolingual semantic similarity, we utilize multilingual sentence transformers (Reimers and Gurevych, 2019, 2020)."
  ],
